<subSubSection pageId="104" pageNumber="105" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="104.[189,454,747,773]" box="[189,454,747,773]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,454,747,773]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,454,747,773]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="104.[188,1399,795,1040]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,537,795,821]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Cheilosia">
<emphasis box="[189,301,795,821]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[318,430,795,821]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Cheilosia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[447,537,796,821]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[544,634,795,821]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most similar to Nepalese species 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1054,1302,795,821]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spuria" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Cheilosia">
<emphasis box="[1054,1166,795,821]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1183,1210,795,821]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1227,1302,796,821]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">spuria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1309,1399,795,821]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and to 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Cheng, 2004" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2004" box="[272,751,831,858]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nadiae" subGenus="Cheilosia">
<emphasis box="[272,298,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[317,344,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[362,442,831,857]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">nadiae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y." box="[451,751,831,857]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" pagination="267 - 416" refId="ref48566" refString="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y. 2004. Revision of the genus Cheilosia Meigen, 1822 (Diptera: Syrphidae) of China. Contributions on Entomology International 5: 267 - 416." type="journal article" year="2004">Barkalov &amp; Cheng, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry box="[946,1020,831,857]" name="China" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">China</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1032,1298,831,858]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Cheilosia">
<emphasis box="[1032,1144,831,857]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1163,1190,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1208,1298,832,857]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1307,1399,832,858]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is distinguished by having an orange basoflagellomere, semi-erect to appressed pilosity on mesonotum and abdomen, a broader frons in anterior part and shorter pilosity on eye. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1087,1251,904,930]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spuria" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Cheilosia">
<emphasis box="[1087,1114,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1132,1158,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1176,1251,905,930]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">spuria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1258,1349,905,931]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2004" box="[189,359,940,967]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nadiae" subGenus="Cheilosia">
<emphasis box="[189,216,941,967]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[234,261,941,967]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[279,359,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">nadiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the basoflagellomere is black, mesonotum and abdomen mostly with erect pilosity, and frons narrower in anterior part, and pilosity of eye is longer. 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[915,1081,977,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spuria" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Cheilosia">
<emphasis box="[915,942,977,1003]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[961,988,977,1003]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1006,1081,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">spuria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1090,1182,977,1003]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2004" box="[190,357,1013,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nadiae" subGenus="Cheilosia">
<emphasis box="[190,217,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[233,260,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[277,357,1013,1039]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">nadiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs in pattern of pollinosity of face and differences of male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="104" pageNumber="105" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="104.[189,324,1080,1106]" box="[189,324,1080,1106]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1080,1106]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1080,1106]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="104.[189,1399,1127,1190]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<emphasis box="[649,750,1128,1153]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">spinosus</emphasis>
’ meaning ‘spiny’ and refers to the presence of a basolateral spur on the fore coxa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
